 \question \emph{Challenge Problem.} Two sides of a triangle have lengths $6cm$ and 
$8cm$. Find an interval for the third side.
	\ifprintanswers
	  \begin{solution}\\
		The basic idea here is that the sum of any $2$ sides of a \emph{triangle} is \emph{always 
bigger} then the third side. Hence, let $x$ be the third side and $6cm$ and $8cm$ being the other 
sides as given in the question, then by this statement, $$6+8>x$$
	  \end{solution}
	\else
	  \makeemptybox{5.7in}
	\fi
